###############################################
# NOTES FOR TESTING
###############################################

# 1. First run the LOGIN request to get JWT token
# 2. Copy the token from response and paste it in the @token variable at the top
# 3. All other requests will use this token automatically
# 4. Make sure the API is running on https://localhost:5142
# 5. You may need to create some test data first (categories, menu items, etc.)
# 6. For order creation, make sure referenced IDs exist in database

###############################################
# STATUS VALUES
###############################################

# Order Status: pending, confirmed, preparing, ready, served, paid, cancelled
# Table Status: available, occupied, reserved
# Discount Type: percent, amount

###############################################
# SAMPLE WORKFLOW
###############################################

# 1. Login to get token
# 2. Create Category
# 3. Create Menu Items
# 4. Create Addons
# 5. Create Discount
# 6. Create Table
# 7. Create Order with items + addons + discount
# 8. Update order status to "paid"


